  "texts": [
    "However, our T-HuBERT (3.1/7.0%) falls behind SpeechLM (2.7/6.2%) on the train-clean-100 subset, which is due to that SpeechLM uses 100 hours of paired data for pre-training, while T-HuBERT does not involve any paired data during the whole training process.To validate the effectiveness of T-HuBERT on the larger datasets, we further conduct fine-tuning experiments using train-clean-360 and train-other-500.",
    "The results presented at the bottom of Table I show that our proposed T-HuBERT also outperforms the baseline HuBERT by a large margin.TABLE II UNIVERSAL SPEECH REPRESENTATION EVALUATION ON THE SUPERB BENCHMARK.",
